gnu.xml
Class QName

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--gnu.xml.QName
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable
public class QName
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable

An XML "qualified name", after namesapce-resolution. Consists of a local part (the part after the colon in an XML file), and a namespace URI (globally-unique name). The prefix of a name (the part before the colon) is not part of a QName, as it is only considered a document-local abbreviation for the namespace URI. QName's are always "interned": if two QNames have the same local part and namespace URI, they are the same QName object.
